The paper proposes a method for multi-exposure image fusion, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The paper discusses the use of a local contrast enhancement method, which is a common technique in computer graphics and image processing. The paper also evaluates the proposed method using tone mapped image quality index, statistical naturalness, and discrete entropy, which are common metrics in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.GR (Graphics), cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
